verbose_text: Finally, rats with acute lung injury induced by intratracheal delivery of lipopolysaccharide (LPS) showed marked elevations in all three cytokines at both the transcript (mean +/- SD fold change to baseline : IL-6, 499 +/- 345; TNFalpha, 18 +/- 18; MCP-1, 36 +/- 20) and protein levels (mean +/- SD fold change to baseline : IL-6, 121 +/- 114; TNFalpha, 402 +/- 343; MCP-1, 30 +/- 15).
evidence: injury induced by intratracheal delivery of lipopolysaccharide
